parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal goes to the floor
the rear brake pedal has no pressure
the rear brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the rear brake fails to engage
air is getting into the brake lines
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front fender can cause the vehicle to vibrate abnormally, making it difficult to steer, and in some cases, can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The front fender vibrates abnormally
the rear portion of the front fender becomes dislodged
the front fender molding becomes dislodged
the front wheel is unable to turn
the steering locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hand hold bracket can cause the bracket to break off, posing a serious threat to the safety of passengers.
symptoms: The hand hold bracket breaks off
the bracket appears to be made from pot metal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: These issues can cause cosmetic damage and potentially lead to more serious problems if left unaddressed.
symptoms: The covering on the seat separates at the seam
the ball on the kickstand flies off
the covering below the hinges of the door
covering the gas filler pipe cracks straight through.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and potentially leaving the driver stranded. Inaccurate fuel level readings can also cause unnecessary stress and distraction while driving.
symptoms: Fuel smell after filling up
inaccurate fuel level readings
fuel gauge not working
fuel gauge reading low fuel when the tank is almost full
fuel gauge light staying on
mileage indicator affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front fender mounting system can cause loss of steering power, wobbling, and potentially lead to accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: Wobbling or shaking of the front end
loss of steering power
rattling or loose front fender
broken or detached front fender
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel support bolt can cause a complete loss of steering power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Complete loss of steering power
wobbling or shaking of the front end
partially detached front wheel support bolt
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.
